        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 10:47PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1044 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near the Tennessee border just south and west of Beech
Mountain, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Excessive rainfall may flood roadside
ditches causing debris to be washed onto the highway.
Flooding of poor drainage areas also possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boone...
Jefferson...
West Jefferson...
Blowing Rock...
Beech Mountain...
Lansing...
and Foscoe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
